        {
          "alias": "characterSource",
          "culture": null,
          "editorAlias": null,
          "segment": null,
          "value": "Destiny 2: Beyond Light"
        },
        {
          "alias": "characterName",
          "culture": null,
          "editorAlias": null,
          "segment": null,
          "value": "Taniks, the Abomination"
        },
        {
          "alias": "details",
          "culture": null,
          "editorAlias": null,
          "segment": null,
          "value": "After being defeated thrice by the same Guardian, Taniks had grown incredibly angry. After his latest defeat during the attempt to take down his killers with him as the Morning Star crashed into Europa, Taniks was seriously damaged and trapped in the wreck. He managed to fuse his body with a Heavy Shank, and fused to it four of the nuclear bombs that would have destroyed Europa if the Guardians hadn\u0027t deactivated them earlier. Reactivating the nukes, and reawakening to face the Guardians one last time, Taniks wielded the moon-destroying powers against his nemeses."
        },
        {
          "alias": "mainPicture",
          "culture": null,
          "editorAlias": null,
          "segment": null,
          "value": [
            {
              "key": "0ef02ae1-e7d7-4eca-8661-e55ac7ab9f50",
