          "segment": null,
          "value": "60"
        },
        {
          "alias": "characterName",
          "culture": null,
          "editorAlias": null,
          "segment": null,
          "value": "Nokris, Herald of Xol"
        },
        {
          "alias": "characterSource",
          "culture": null,
          "editorAlias": null,
          "segment": null,
          "value": "Destiny 2: Warmind"
        },
        {
          "alias": "details",
          "culture": null,
          "editorAlias": null,
          "segment": null,
          "value": "Nokris was the second son born to Oryx. In his attempts to grow strong in order to contend with his strong siblings, he sought out the mysterious powers of Necromancy. He managed to perfect his skills with this power, but due to going against the Sword Logic Oryx disowned and banished Nokris. The unfavored son would then ally with Xol, Will of the Thousands, and together they grew a powerful brood. He was revered as a God like his siblings before his banishment, and was a member of Oryx\u0027s Court at the time of the fall of the Gift Mast."
        },
        {
          "alias": "profilePicture",
          "culture": null,
          "editorAlias": null,
          "segment": null,
          "value": [
            {
              "key": "820975a5-b666-42db-95ab-0e8d4912f6a8",
